messages.message: Hi folks, just an FYI we have made the docs on dogfood publicly available (meaning no log in required), and will do the same for the docs on instabase.com (http://instabase.com) ahead of the AIHub launch cc @Kerry
It’s still the same link, https://dogfood.instabase.com/docs
just FYI the docs currently there is a separate copy of the docs that you see when you log in. this separate copy is in 23.01

Ashwin and I were testing the routing part out on dogfood (the design agency for our public website has helped us set up the folder structure in the server using the files we gave them a whiel ago). When the doc is out in prod, it'll be 23.04. cc @jean

so the behavior is -- if you are logged into dogfood, you'll see the dogfood doc which has CICD. when you use an incognito window, you'll see a separate copy that currently can only be updated manually
Oh, this explains some weird behavior we were just puzzling over on dogfood!
I am waiting for a couple of things to be merged for the 23.04 docs, @Kerry, but can get those built and to you this afternoon.
actually right now on dogfood, it always goes to that separate 23.01 copy it seems; we can set this up later
